'''Haris Smaji<U+0107>''' (born 8 March 1960) is a former [[Bosnia and Herzegovina|Bosnian]] [[association football|football]] player. He played for [[Yugoslavia national under-20 football team]] at the [[1979 FIFA World Youth Championship]],<ref name="fifa">{{cite web|url=http://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/statisticsandrecords/players/player=192438/index.html|title=FIFA Player Statistics: Haris SMAJIC|work=[[FIFA]]|accessdate=31 July 2010}}</ref> but was never capped for [[Yugoslavia national football team|Yugoslavia]] at full international level.

A product of [[FK Sarajevo]] academy, Smaji<U+0107> played for the team between 1978 and 1983 in the [[Yugoslav First League]], after which he played a season with the second level side [[KF Prishtina|FK Pri<U+0161>tina]].

